The paper focuses on the performance of deep convolutional neural networks for image classification, which is primarily related to computer vision (cs.CV). The experiments involve training networks to learn the arithmetic addition of two integers, which is a task related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the networks' ability to reason autonomously, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
